<paragraph id="25262F0E1026FFB9DBB2F8624D762C69" blockId="3.[151,477,1797,1860]" box="[151,323,1833,1860]" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">
(
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1026FFB9DBBAF8624CD32C6E" box="[159,230,1833,1859]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1810,1834]" captionTargetBox="[160,1428,181,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-29@4.[160,1428,181,1786]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Asianthrips species. (1) A. balianus, female (mac). (2) A. bamboosielloides, female (mac). A. bicolor, 3–4; (3) Female (mac); (4) Female (mic). (5) A. borneoensis, female (mac). A. dasycornis, 6–7; (6) Female (mac); (7) Male (mic). A. denticornis, 8–9; (8) Male (mac); (9) Female (mic). (10) A. longior, female (mac)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404866" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404866/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1026FFB9DBD1F8624D092C69" box="[244,316,1833,1860]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–35" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1810,1834]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,181,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[160,1427,181,1786]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 29–35. Asianthrips balianus, sp. n., female (mac). (29) Head &amp; pronotum; (30) Antenna; (31) Basantra– mesopresternum; (32) Metanotum; (33) Fore wing, subbasal setae; (34) Pelta &amp; tergite II; (35) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404878" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404878/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">29–35</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="25262F0E1026FFBCDBB2F83A4FE82CDD" blockId="3.[151,1437,1905,2004]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,1466,2033]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="107" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1026FFB9DBB2F83A4D4E2CA6" box="[151,379,1905,1931]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Female macroptera.</emphasis>
<materialsCitation id="95F125531026FFBCDAA7F83A4FEF2CDD" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3744622318" collectionCode="VII, III, IV, VIII" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="107" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" specimenCount="5" typeStatus="holotype">
Body largely yellowish (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1026FFB9D9B0F83A4EE22CA6" box="[661,727,1905,1931]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1810,1834]" captionTargetBox="[160,1428,181,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-29@4.[160,1428,181,1786]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Asianthrips species. (1) A. balianus, female (mac). (2) A. bamboosielloides, female (mac). A. bicolor, 3–4; (3) Female (mac); (4) Female (mic). (5) A. borneoensis, female (mac). A. dasycornis, 6–7; (6) Female (mac); (7) Male (mic). A. denticornis, 8–9; (8) Male (mac); (9) Female (mic). (10) A. longior, female (mac)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404866" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404866/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), but mesothorax and anterior angles of abdominal segments II to 
<collectionCode id="4388B7CB1026FFB9DB90F8DD4CE92C9D" box="[181,220,1942,1968]" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">VII</collectionCode>
brownish. Head more or less brownish, a little darker than prothorax. Tube brownish subbasally. Antennal segments I and II pale brown, segment 
<collectionCode id="4388B7CB1026FFB9D96AF8F14E5E2CF9" box="[591,619,1978,2004]" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">III</collectionCode>
yellowish, very weakly shaded distally, segments 
<collectionCode id="4388B7CB1026FFB9DF85F8F148882CF9" box="[1184,1213,1978,2004]" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">IV</collectionCode>
to 
<collectionCode id="4388B7CB1026FFB9DFC4F8F148CB2CF9" box="[1249,1278,1978,2004]" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">IV</collectionCode>
brown, with basal 1/4–1/3 yellowish, segments 
<collectionCode id="4388B7CB1023FFBCD906FAF04E7F2EF8" box="[547,586,1467,1493]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">VII</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode id="4388B7CB1023FFBCD9A7FAF04E872EF8" box="[642,690,1467,1493]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">VIII</collectionCode>
uniformly brown. All femora weakly shaded with brown distally, all tibiae and tarsi yellow. Fore wings shaded with brown, but pale at base and median constriction. Prominent body setae almost colourless. Head (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1023FFBCD915F9494EB72D30" box="[560,642,1538,1565]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–35" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1810,1834]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,181,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[160,1427,181,1786]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 29–35. Asianthrips balianus, sp. n., female (mac). (29) Head &amp; pronotum; (30) Antenna; (31) Basantra– mesopresternum; (32) Metanotum; (33) Fore wing, subbasal setae; (34) Pelta &amp; tergite II; (35) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404878" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404878/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) a little wider than long, 0.95 times as long as wide in 
<typeStatus id="FA2291AC1023FFBCDFC2F94949782D31" box="[1255,1357,1538,1564]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">holotype</typeStatus>
; dorsal surface sculptured with transverse reticulation, but weak. Cheeks very weakly rounded, weakly narrowed to base. Postocular setae a little shorter than eye. Eyes 0.43–0.44 times as long as head in 
<typeStatus id="FA2291AC1023FFBCDF0FF90148A52D49" box="[1066,1168,1610,1636]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">holotype</typeStatus>
. Antennal segments 
<collectionCode id="4388B7CB1023FFBCDE50F90049A92D48" box="[1397,1436,1611,1637]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">VII</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode id="4388B7CB1023FFBCDBEDF9244CCD2DA4" box="[200,248,1647,1673]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">VIII</collectionCode>
somewhat narrowly fused, segment 
<collectionCode id="4388B7CB1023FFBCD9B8F9244EF82DA4" box="[669,717,1647,1673]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">VIII</collectionCode>
lanceolate, distinctly constricted at base (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1023FFBCDF88F92549312DA4" box="[1197,1284,1646,1673]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–35" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1810,1834]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,181,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[160,1427,181,1786]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 29–35. Asianthrips balianus, sp. n., female (mac). (29) Head &amp; pronotum; (30) Antenna; (31) Basantra– mesopresternum; (32) Metanotum; (33) Fore wing, subbasal setae; (34) Pelta &amp; tergite II; (35) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404878" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404878/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
); segment 
<collectionCode id="4388B7CB1023FFBCDEA5F92449A92DA4" box="[1408,1436,1647,1673]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">III</collectionCode>
with three sense cones. Maxillary stylets short and V-shaped, retracted into 1/4 of head capsule; maxillary bridge distinct, but narrow and arched. Mouth cone rather pointed. Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1023FFBCD8F4F9FD48102DFC" box="[977,1061,1718,1745]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–35" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1810,1834]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,181,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[160,1427,181,1786]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 29–35. Asianthrips balianus, sp. n., female (mac). (29) Head &amp; pronotum; (30) Antenna; (31) Basantra– mesopresternum; (32) Metanotum; (33) Fore wing, subbasal setae; (34) Pelta &amp; tergite II; (35) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404878" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404878/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) 0.67 times as long as head and 1.85 times as wide as long in 
<typeStatus id="FA2291AC1023FFBCDAC9F9914E672DD9" box="[492,594,1754,1780]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">holotype</typeStatus>
; pa and epim subequal in length, about 1/2 of the median pronotal length. Metanotum (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1023FFBCDA0FF9B54D482C34" box="[298,381,1790,1817]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–35" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1810,1834]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,181,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[160,1427,181,1786]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 29–35. Asianthrips balianus, sp. n., female (mac). (29) Head &amp; pronotum; (30) Antenna; (31) Basantra– mesopresternum; (32) Metanotum; (33) Fore wing, subbasal setae; (34) Pelta &amp; tergite II; (35) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404878" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404878/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
) sculptured with polygonal reticulation, but very weak. Prospinasternum weakly developed, eroded. Mesopresternum and mesoeusternum widely fused (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1023FFBCD819F8694FBA2C10" box="[828,911,1826,1853]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–35" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1810,1834]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,181,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[160,1427,181,1786]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 29–35. Asianthrips balianus, sp. n., female (mac). (29) Head &amp; pronotum; (30) Antenna; (31) Basantra– mesopresternum; (32) Metanotum; (33) Fore wing, subbasal setae; (34) Pelta &amp; tergite II; (35) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404878" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404878/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
), with indistinct short sutures between them at both sides. Fore tarsi unarmed. Fore wings with 5–5 duplicated cilia. Pelta (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1023FFBCD8FBF80D481B2C4C" box="[990,1070,1862,1889]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–35" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1810,1834]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,181,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[160,1427,181,1786]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 29–35. Asianthrips balianus, sp. n., female (mac). (29) Head &amp; pronotum; (30) Antenna; (31) Basantra– mesopresternum; (32) Metanotum; (33) Fore wing, subbasal setae; (34) Pelta &amp; tergite II; (35) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404878" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404878/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
) weakly developed, bell-shaped. Tergites well developed, tergites II to 
<collectionCode id="4388B7CB1023FFBCD962F8204E5B2CA8" box="[583,622,1899,1925]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">VII</collectionCode>
wider than pronotum; a median pair of setae well developed, almost as long as or a little longer than wing retaining setae on same tergite. S1 setae on tergite IX shorter than S2, 0.72–0.76 times as long as tube in 
<typeStatus id="FA2291AC1023FFBCDA82F8F94E392CE1" box="[423,524,1970,1996]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">holotype</typeStatus>
, S1 weakly expanded or blunt, S2 blunt or nearly pointed at apex. Tube (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1023FFBCDE67F8F949A12CE0" box="[1346,1428,1970,1997]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–35" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1810,1834]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,181,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[160,1427,181,1786]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 29–35. Asianthrips balianus, sp. n., female (mac). (29) Head &amp; pronotum; (30) Antenna; (31) Basantra– mesopresternum; (32) Metanotum; (33) Fore wing, subbasal setae; (34) Pelta &amp; tergite II; (35) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404878" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404878/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
) 0.57 times as long as head in 
<typeStatus id="FA2291AC1023FFBCDAC4F89D4E722CDD" box="[481,583,2006,2032]" pageId="6" pageNumber="107">holotype</typeStatus>
. Anal setae a little shorter than tube
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<caption id="71E67F861021FFBEDBB2F8594FEF2C5F" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404866" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6404866" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404866/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="105" startId="4.[151,264,1810,1834]" targetBox="[160,1428,181,1786]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="25262F0E1021FFBEDBB2F8594FEF2C5F" blockId="4.[151,1437,1810,1906]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1021FFBEDBB2F8594D7C2C07" bold="true" box="[151,329,1810,1834]" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">FIGURES 1–10.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="E299548D1021FFBEDA75F8594E282C07" box="[336,541,1810,1834]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1021FFBEDA75F8594DF02C07" box="[336,453,1810,1834]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="105">Asianthrips</emphasis>
species.
