<subSubSection id="6D837C85102DFFB2DBE2FE6C4FE22A80" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="25262F0E102DFFB2DBE2FE6C4FE22A80" blockId="8.[151,1437,150,429]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C102DFFB2DBE2FE6C4D012A6C" bold="true" box="[199,308,295,321]" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D102DFFB2DA67FE6C4DF52A6C" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[322,448,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balianus">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C102DFFB2DA67FE6C4DF52A6C" box="[322,448,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">A. balianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has slender antennal segment VIII which is narrowly fused to the segment VII (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B102DFFB2DE19FE6C49BA2A6C" box="[1340,1423,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–35" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1810,1834]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,181,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[160,1427,181,1786]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 29–35. Asianthrips balianus, sp. n., female (mac). (29) Head &amp; pronotum; (30) Antenna; (31) Basantra– mesopresternum; (32) Metanotum; (33) Fore wing, subbasal setae; (34) Pelta &amp; tergite II; (35) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404878" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404878/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
), rather short head and short and V-shaped maxillary stylets (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B102DFFB2D819FE004FA42A48" box="[828,913,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–35" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1810,1834]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,181,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[160,1427,181,1786]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 29–35. Asianthrips balianus, sp. n., female (mac). (29) Head &amp; pronotum; (30) Antenna; (31) Basantra– mesopresternum; (32) Metanotum; (33) Fore wing, subbasal setae; (34) Pelta &amp; tergite II; (35) Tube." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404878" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404878/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
), and these character states are shared with 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D102DFFB2DEA1FE004D1D2AA5" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="109" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vietnamensis">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C102DFFB2DEA1FE004D1D2AA5" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="109">A. vietnamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, newly described below. From that species, however, it is easily distinguished by having three sense cones on the antennal segment III and largely yellow body colour (
